        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When having attributes in the topmost element of an xml file, they are not parsed by Zend_Config_Xml (ZF 1.9 beta1)\ne.g.:\n{noformat}\n$string = <<<EOT\n<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<configdata test=\"test\">\n    <someconfig webhost=\"www.example.com\">\n    <\/someconfig>\n    <anotherconfig extends=\"someconfig\">\n    <\/anotherconfig>\n<\/configdata>\nEOT;\n$config = new Zend_Config_Xml($string);\nvar_dump($config->toArray());\n{noformat}\nwould output\n{noformat}\narray\n  'someconfig' => \n    array\n      'webhost' => string 'www.example.com' (length=15)\n  'anotherconfig' => \n    array\n      'webhost' => string 'www.example.com' (length=15)\n{noformat}\ninstead of\n{noformat}\narray\n  'someconfig' => \n    array\n      'webhost' => string 'www.example.com' (length=15)\n  'anotherconfig' => \n    array\n      'webhost' => string 'www.example.com' (length=15)\n  'test' => string 'test' (length=4)\n{noformat}\nI think the simplest way to solve this would be adding the following after line 106:\n{noformat}\n            foreach ($config->attributes() as $name => $value)\n            {\n            \t$dataArray[$name] = (string) $value;\n            }\n{noformat}"
        },
