        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32958",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm fairly certain this is an issue due to how PHP's DOM library handles the root node of an XML file, but I'll leave the final resolution to Rob and\/or Ben.\n\nIt's more reliable to simply have a child node with that value.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-26T15:04:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-26T15:04:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32959",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "No, actually this would be possible, tho at the moment, Zend_Config_Xml always assumes the first level nodes (within the root node) to be sections, and a section cannot be a string value but a parent of nodes. I have to see if I will find a way around that when refactoring Zend_Config_Xml.\n\nBut seriously, according to this example, sections are used here, so I don't see a reason for a text-section.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-26T16:18:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-26T16:18:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32961",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=loladiro",
                        "name": "loladiro",
                        "displayName": "Keno Fischer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well, this only is a problem when you have config files that don't make use of sections. Another problem (for me) is that \"$thisSection  = $element->$section;\" at line 156 always refers to the same element even if there are multiple elements with this name in the section.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=loladiro",
                        "name": "loladiro",
                        "displayName": "Keno Fischer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-27T00:53:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-27T00:53:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/46825",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Not a supported use case. Top level keys in Zend_Config_Xml are sections.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-05-27T02:27:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-05-27T02:27:30.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
